You can use register Function Bean which will work as a Lambda and supports all Spring Boot features.

Create a Function with @Bean annotation

```java
@Bean
public Function&lt;String, String&gt; uppercase() {
  return value -&gt; {
      return value.toUpperCase();
  };
}
```

By default, this Bean will work as Lambda.

You also need to add `org.springframework.cloud.function.adapter.aws.FunctionInvoker::handleReques` as handler in AWS Lambda.

If you want to use the same codebase with multiple `Bean` `Function` as Lambda then you can conditionally enable `Bean` as follows:

```java
@Bean
@ConditionalOnProperty(name=&quot;active.lambda&quot;, havingValue=&quot;MyLambdaOne&quot;)
public Function&lt;String, String&gt; uppercase() {
  return value -&gt; {
      return value.toUpperCase();
  };
}
```

**Reference:**

[Official Spring Doc](https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-static/spring-cloud-function/3.0.6.RELEASE/reference/html/spring-cloud-function.html#_aws_lambda)

